        "create_time": 1722821332.958614,
        "update_time": null,
        "content": {
          "content_type": "text",
          "parts": [
            "To say \"prepare for the case of war, unknown\" in Latin, you can use the following phrase:\n\n\"Para ad casum belli ignoti.\"\n\nHere’s the breakdown:\n- \"Para\" means \"prepare.\"\n- \"ad casum\" means \"for the case.\"\n- \"belli\" means \"of war.\"\n- \"ignoti\" means \"unknown.\""
          ]
        },
